TryHackMe - Networking and Security Tools
Today I learned about Internet-connected devices, threat intelligence tools, and vulnerability management.
Internet of Things (IoT)
IoT stands for Internet of Things.
These are physical devices that connect to the Internet and exchange data.
Examples include smart cameras, smart TVs, smart watches, and other connected devices.
As more devices connect to the Internet, securing them becomes increasingly important.
Shodan
I learned about Shodan.
Shodan is a search engine that helps identify devices exposed to the Internet.
It can be used to find:
Servers
Routers
Cameras
IoT devices
Other Internet-facing systems
Shodan allows filtering results by country, organization, hostname, ports, and other attributes.
This helps security professionals understand what systems are publicly accessible.
VirusTotal
VirusTotal is a platform used by security professionals to analyze files, URLs, domains, and IP addresses.
It aggregates results from many antivirus vendors and security companies.
If a suspicious file is uploaded, VirusTotal shows how different security engines classify it.
This makes it useful for threat intelligence and malware analysis.
Vulnerability Databases
I learned that known vulnerabilities are stored in vulnerability databases.
These databases help security professionals identify and track security weaknesses.
A vulnerability is a weakness that could potentially be exploited by an attacker.
CIA Triad
Security professionals often evaluate the impact of vulnerabilities using three principles:
Confidentiality
Protecting sensitive information from unauthorized access.
Integrity
Ensuring information is not modified or tampered with.
Availability
Ensuring systems and services remain accessible when needed.
CVSS
CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System) helps measure the severity of vulnerabilities.
The score considers factors such as:
Attack complexity
Privileges required
User interaction
Impact on confidentiality
Impact on integrity
Impact on availability
Higher scores indicate more serious vulnerabilities.
CVE
CVE stands for Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures.
Each publicly known vulnerability receives a unique identifier.
Example:
Plain text
CVE-2021-44228
This allows security professionals worldwide to reference the same vulnerability consistently.
Linux Documentation
I also learned about the man command.
Bash
man ping
The man command displays documentation and usage information for Linux commands.
Reading documentation is an important skill because security professionals often rely on manuals and technical guides to understand tools and systems.
Key Takeaways
IoT devices are Internet-connected physical devices.
Shodan helps discover Internet-facing systems.
VirusTotal aggregates malware detection results from many vendors.
Vulnerabilities are tracked through databases and CVEs.
The CIA triad consists of Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability.
CVSS measures vulnerability severity.
Documentation and manual pages are essential resources for learning technical tools.
